### ‚ùì Retrieve Booking Details (After Deletion)

Trying to fetch a booking that may have been removed? This endpoint checks for the existence of a booking using its ID. It's a great way to verify whether a deletion actually succeeded. üïµÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èüóÇÔ∏è

---

#### üì¨ Request

- **Method:** `GET`


``` bash
https://{{URL}}/booking/:id
 ```

Replace `:id` with the unique booking identifier you're looking for.

---

#### üßæ URL Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `:id` | string | The unique ID of the booking |

---

#### üì¶ Response

The response is a JSON object containing all booking details‚Äî**if the booking exists**. If the booking was successfully deleted earlier, this request is likely to return a `404 Not Found` or an empty result.

